
# Contribution Guidelines

Thank you for considering contributing to Blueprint! We appreciate your interest in helping to improve this project. Please take a moment to review the following guidelines to ensure a smooth contribution process.


## How to Contribute

1. Fork the repository to your GitHub account.
2. Clone the forked repository to your local machine:

~~~bash
git clone https://github.com/cicerotcv/blueprint.git
~~~

3. Create a new branch for your contribution:

4. Make your changes and commit them with clear and descriptive messages. We follow the [conventional commits specification](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) for our commit messages. Conventional commits provide a structured way to describe the purpose of a commit and its type.

5. Push your changes to your fork.
 
6. Submit a pull request (PR) to the main branch of the main repository. Be sure to include a detailed description of your changes in the PR.

## Development Setup

To set up the development environment:

1. Install `pnpm`:

~~~bash
npm install -g pnpm
~~~

2. Install dependencies:

~~~bash
pnpm install
~~~

2. Make your changes.

3. Run `prettier`:

~~~bash
pnpm run prettier:write
~~~

4. Run tests to ensure your changes didn't break anything:

~~~bash
pnpm run tests:run
~~~

If you're adding new features or modifying existing ones, make sure to update the documentation and tests accordingly.

## Coding Guidelines

- Follow the existing code style and conventions.
- Write clear, concise, and well-documented code.
- Write meaningful commit messages that describe the purpose of your changes.
- Ensure that your changes pass all tests.